caller_intent: Jay is trying to add a car to his insurance policy with full coverage but is encountering a system error that prevents him from doing so. He believes the issue may be related to his daughter's accident history or the type of vehicle.
resolution_steps: Agent acknowledges the system error preventing full coverage addition.
Agent checks the system and confirms no accident record is present for the daughter.
Agent hypothesizes the issue may be related to the vehicle type or other system-specific restrictions.
Agent offers to verify directly with the insurance company to resolve the blockage.
Agent requests time to follow up with the company and promises to return with confirmation.
knowledge_required: Understanding of insurance system error codes and coverage restrictions
Knowledge of how accident records and vehicle types affect coverage eligibility
Process for verifying policy details directly with the insurance carrier
summary: Jay is unable to add a vehicle to his insurance policy due to a system error blocking full coverage. The agent is investigating potential causes (accident history, vehicle type) and will verify directly with the carrier. Resolution requires further confirmation from the insurance company.
